      <h1>PCTN Game</h1>
      <div class="info-flex">
        <div>
          <p>One of my proudest achievements and a true example of what I stand for. This "choose your own adventure game" was a result of coming up for a fun, engaging, and innovative way of presenting centain concept and stories for the course Postcolonial Transitions and Transnational Justice during my MA Gender Studies.</p>
          <p>Along with 5 other amazing classmates, we wanted to create an experience were one is confronted by the inability of choice as a result of coliniality, imperialism, and Eurocentrism. Taking the true story of Pocahontas, with her real name being Amonute, which has been altered greatly in our collective minds by Disney, the player is put in her shoes and has to make choices as British colonizers force themselves onto her community and land.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>The game was a huge success during class. With many classmates being frustrated once they quickly figured out that their choices were to no avail. There is no happy ending, only exploitation caused by power imbalance and the greed of men. I highly reccomend you checking it out yourself <a href="https://annaboter.github.io/PCTN-presentation-game/">here!</a></p>
        </div>
